• Nutrition and Health: Macronutrients and Overnutrition

     335 reviews

    Learn from the top professors of Wageningen University & Research about macronutrients and overnutrition and how they impact humans. This online course is offered as a MOOC, and is part of the Professional Certificate Pogramme: Nutrition and Health.

    • edX
    • 9 weeks, 6-8 hours a week
    • On-Demand
    • Free Online Course (Audit)

  • Nutrition and Health: Food Safety

     186 reviews

    Learn about bacteria, pesticides and health hazards present in food. This online course is offered as a MOOC which means that you can study at your own pace, at your own time and anywhere you want.

    • edX
    • 8 weeks, 6-8 hours a week
    • On-Demand
    • Free Online Course (Audit)

  • Sustainable Tourism: Society & Environmental Aspects

     178 reviews

    Explore the societal and environmental impacts of tourism in this 6-week course by Wageningen University. Learn about sustainable practices, history, and the effects of global events on tourism.

    • 6 weeks, 5-7 hours a week
    • On-Demand
    • Free Online Course (Audit)

  • Nutrition and Health: Human Microbiome

     730 reviews

    Learn how you can impact your health by balancing your gut health; how your microbiome together with your diet can improve normal gut function. A balanced microbiome and nutritional intake can avoid disorders like IBS, obesity and diabetes.

    • edX
    • 6 weeks, 3-5 hours a week
    • On-Demand
    • Free Online Course (Audit)

    • Best of All Time

     324 reviews

    Explore the role of nutrition in cancer prevention and progression with Wageningen University's 5-week course. Ideal for health professionals and cancer survivors.

    • 5 weeks, 6-8 hours a week
    • On-Demand
    • Free Online Course (Audit)

  • HOPE: What Makes Us Human

     292 reviews

    What sets us apart, and brings us together, as humans? How can we live up to our humanity? HOPE is an open invitation to become better at being human, to realize our humanity. Join HOPE to discover what it means to be us and live up to it!

    • Free Online Course (Audit)
